{
  "description": {
    "title": "Endogenous investment on a competitive path: decision year vs effective year (small, fast)",
    "paper": "PLANiT K-MSR working paper (July 2026), Section 6 / Appendix A.7, A.10: an irreversible investor commits not at the Marshallian break-even theta but at the Dixit-Pindyck trigger P* = M(sigma_eff, r, y) * theta; at sigma = 0 the multiple keeps the pure timing wedge M = r/y (NOT 1). Feature spec: docs/invest-feedback-spec.md D1-D2 (trigger-consistent adoption equilibrium, delivered-price signal).",
    "mechanism": "investment_feedback_enabled arms the outer adoption loop (engine/feedback.py): each iteration masks un-adopted flagged technology options, re-runs the FULL competitive path solve, and dates at most one trigger crossing on the DELIVERED price path (one flip per iteration, monotone, <= N_flagged + 1 iterations). The flagged option's investment_trigger block IS the flag; build_lag_years = 1 separates the DECISION year tau (state flips, 'Investment Adoptions' column) from the EFFECTIVE year tau + 1 ('Investment Newly Effective' column) - capacity only enters the choice set at tau + L.",
    "inputs": "One participant (Steel, BAU 100 Mt, linear MAC slope 2), one flagged option H2-DRI (BAU 70 Mt - a 30% cleaner fleet - same MAC slope, replaces the base technology on adoption). Caps 70 -> 42 Mt over 2026-2030 (derive_from_cap, no free allocation), r = 5.5%. Trigger: theta = 48, payout_yield y = 0.03, sigma = 0 -> M = r/y = 11/6 exactly, P* = 88; build lag 1 year.",
    "expected_output": {
      "masked (pre-adoption) prices 2026-2030": [60.0, 76.0, 90.0, 104.0, 116.0],
      "delivered prices 2026-2030": [60.0, 76.0, 90.0, 44.0, 56.0],
      "adoption": "decision year 2028 (first P_t >= 88 on the masked path: 90), capacity effective 2029 (lag 1). Investment Newly Effective = [0, 0, 0, 1, 0]; 2 outer iterations; converged.",
      "reading": "Clearing is hand-invertible: masked years P_t = 2*(100 - S_t); post-effective years P_t = 2*(70 - S_t). The 2028 row shows the DECISION (state flips, price still 90 = masked value because capacity arrives only at tau + L); 2029 shows the entrant capacity repricing the market from 104 to 44 - discrete entry depresses the post-adoption price below the trigger, the spec D1.1 ex-post asymmetry."
    },
